if (!isNaN(num)) {
  // Calculate the factorial and display the result
  const factorial = calculateFactorial(num);
  console.log(`The factorial of ${num} is ${factorial}`);
} else {
  console.log("Invalid input. Please enter a valid number.");
}
This program defines a function calculateFactorial that uses recursion to calculate the factorial of a number. It also uses the prompt function to take user input, converts the input to a number using parseInt, and then displays the factorial of the entered number. If the user enters an invalid input, it provides an error message.




