// Function to add two numbers
function addNumbers(a, b) {
  return a + b;
}

// Example usage
const number1 = 5;
const number2 = 10;
const sum = addNumbers(number1, number2);

console.log(`The sum of ${number1} and ${number2} is ${sum}`);
In this example, the addNumbers function takes two parameters, a and b, and returns their sum. The console.log statement is used to display the result of the addition. You can call this function with different sets of numbers to add them together.





